{
  "segments": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 1.9,
      "text": "Again, I should go double check this"
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "start": 1.9,
      "end": 3.4,
      "text": "to what Mongo does today."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "start": 5.54,
      "end": 6.94,
      "text": "Obviously, you'll find out."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "start": 6.94,
      "end": 9.0,
      "text": "It looks like they might be trying to do stuff"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "start": 9.0,
      "end": 10.04,
      "text": "with actual hospitals."
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "start": 10.04,
      "end": 10.88,
      "text": "Okay."
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "start": 12.72,
      "end": 15.68,
      "text": "When I talk to them before the pandemic,"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "start": 15.68,
      "end": 19.04,
      "text": "they didn't have like any logical physical operators,"
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "start": 19.04,
      "end": 21.56,
      "text": "which is like, here's like JSON stuff, I think."
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "start": 22.96,
      "end": 27.36,
      "text": "Copper GP, rewrote from scratch, their query optimizer,"
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "start": 27.36,
      "end": 28.04,
      "text": "they're just like a renel,"
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "start": 28.04,
      "end": 29.12,
      "text": "so they started with something that was based on"
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "start": 29.12,
      "end": 32.88,
      "text": "logistics, and then they wrote one that based on cascades."
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "start": 32.88,
      "end": 34.48,
      "text": "Everything's written and go,"
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "start": 34.48,
      "end": 39.3,
      "text": "and they're more pure to the cascades model"
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "start": 39.3,
      "end": 40.96,
      "text": "than the maybe Microsoft was,"
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "start": 40.96,
      "end": 43.48,
      "text": "because they would have a DSL that specifies"
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "start": 43.48,
      "end": 46.56,
      "text": "here's the rules and then and the transformations."
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "start": 46.56,
      "end": 48.48,
      "text": "And in some cases where you can't do"
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "start": 48.48,
      "end": 50.88,
      "text": "the transformation entirely through their DSL,"
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "start": 51.84,
      "end": 54.64,
      "text": "you could escape into go code."
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "start": 54.64,
      "end": 58.52,
      "text": "So here's basically what their rules sort of look like, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "start": 58.52,
      "end": 62.36,
      "text": "So you have like the matching that you want at this DSL,"
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "start": 62.36,
      "end": 64.32,
      "text": "and then other things you may want to apply,"
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "start": 64.32,
      "end": 67.0,
      "text": "and then this then gets transpiled into go"
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "start": 67.0,
      "end": 68.88,
      "text": "that they've been run into the system."
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "start": 71.4,
      "end": 76.32,
      "text": "All right, let me run, rush through randomize really quick,"
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "start": 76.32,
      "end": 79.84,
      "text": "because again, this exists, Postgres does this."
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "start": 81.32,
      "end": 84.48,
      "text": "So, rather than doing top down or bottom up,"
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "start": 84.48,
      "end": 86.64,
      "text": "what if you just did a random walk?"
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "start": 86.64,
      "end": 88.76,
      "text": "So you got to start with some query plan,"
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "start": 88.76,
      "end": 90.36,
      "text": "and that one, you can just,"
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "start": 90.36,
      "end": 93.96,
      "text": "you're a straight conversion of the AST"
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "start": 93.96,
      "end": 96.04,
      "text": "from a logical plan into physical plan,"
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "start": 96.04,
      "end": 97.52,
      "text": "and just permute that."
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "start": 97.52,
      "end": 100.88,
      "text": "But the idea is that you look at a bunch"
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "start": 100.88,
      "end": 103.68,
      "text": "of different possible query plans,"
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "start": 104.88,
      "end": 107.08,
      "text": "pick where everyone has the best cost,"
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "start": 107.08,
      "end": 111.2,
      "text": "keep track of that, throw away the ones that are the lowest cost,"
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "start": 111.2,
      "end": 113.48,
      "text": "do some kind of randomization or permutation on it"
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "start": 113.48,
      "end": 115.48,
      "text": "to then change things,"
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "start": 115.48,
      "end": 117.4,
      "text": "and then do another round and check a liver again."
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "start": 117.4,
      "end": 118.48,
      "text": "So you're just randomly walking,"
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "start": 118.48,
      "end": 120.92,
      "text": "and you just try to see whether you stumble upon"
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "start": 120.92,
      "end": 121.92,
      "text": "the best query plan."
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "start": 123.04,
      "end": 125.6,
      "text": "So there's an early paper in 1987"
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "start": 125.6,
      "end": 127.28,
      "text": "that does this with simulated annealing."
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "start": 127.28,
      "end": 129.24,
      "text": "Again, the idea is that you,"
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "start": 129.24,
      "end": 131.76,
      "text": "you just swapping operators and like,"
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "start": 131.76,
      "end": 133.92,
      "text": "the join ordering of two tables randomly,"
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "start": 134.96,
      "end": 136.16,
      "text": "if the plan makes it worse,"
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "start": 136.16,
      "end": 139.36,
      "text": "then you flip away the coin and see whether,"
    },
    {
      "id": 52,
      "start": 139.36,
      "end": 142.08,
      "text": "you should keep pursuing that down that path,"
    },
    {
      "id": 53,
      "start": 142.08,
      "end": 143.72,
      "text": "otherwise you flip it back."
    },
    {
      "id": 54,
      "start": 143.72,
      "end": 145.12,
      "text": "Now there's a bunch of rules you got to write"
    },
    {
      "id": 55,
      "start": 145.12,
      "end": 147.04,
      "text": "to make sure that you don't do things like,"
    },
    {
      "id": 56,
      "start": 147.04,
      "end": 148.8,
      "text": "if it's a left out or join,"
    },
    {
      "id": 57,
      "start": 148.8,
      "end": 151.52,
      "text": "where you have to care about one being joined for the other,"
    },
    {
      "id": 58,
      "start": 151.52,
      "end": 153.84,
      "text": "you don't put things in the wrong order."
    },
    {
      "id": 59,
      "start": 153.84,
      "end": 157.48,
      "text": "So you have to check to see whether the random change"
    },
    {
      "id": 60,
      "start": 157.48,
      "end": 159.24,
      "text": "is actually still a correct plan,"
    },
    {
      "id": 61,
      "start": 159.24,
      "end": 160.76,
      "text": "but then if it doesn't get violated,"
    },
    {
      "id": 62,
      "start": 160.76,
      "end": 162.64,
      "text": "then you can flip things around, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 63,
      "start": 163.64,
      "end": 164.56,
      "text": "Nobody does this."
    },
    {
      "id": 64,
      "start": 166.32,
      "end": 169.08,
      "text": "What Post-Cos does do is use a genetic algorithm."
    },
    {
      "id": 65,
      "start": 169.08,
      "end": 172.08,
      "text": "I think this was introduced in the mid 2000s."
    },
    {
      "id": 66,
      "start": 173.48,
      "end": 174.8,
      "text": "So there are going to use a genetic algorithm"
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "start": 174.88,
      "end": 176.16,
      "text": "where you're going to have these different generations"
    },
    {
      "id": 68,
      "start": 176.16,
      "end": 177.2,
      "text": "of different query plans."
    },
    {
      "id": 69,
      "start": 177.2,
      "end": 179.08,
      "text": "Then you pick which one is the best,"
    },
    {
      "id": 70,
      "start": 179.08,
      "end": 180.04,
      "text": "throw away the ones that are worse,"
    },
    {
      "id": 71,
      "start": 180.04,
      "end": 181.68,
      "text": "then permute the best ones to try to,"
    },
    {
      "id": 72,
      "start": 182.96,
      "end": 186.72,
      "text": "try to find the traits or the genes of the query plans"
    },
    {
      "id": 73,
      "start": 186.72,
      "end": 188.56,
      "text": "that make it a good query plan,"
    },
    {
      "id": 74,
      "start": 188.56,
      "end": 191.52,
      "text": "and then hope that you sort of stumble upon the best one,"
    },
    {
      "id": 75,
      "start": 191.52,
      "end": 192.36,
      "text": "right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 76,
      "start": 192.36,
      "end": 193.2,
      "text": "So Post-Cos does this,"
    },
    {
      "id": 77,
      "start": 193.2,
      "end": 194.6,
      "text": "but you only get it when you have,"
    },
    {
      "id": 78,
      "start": 194.6,
      "end": 198.16,
      "text": "you give it a query that has more than 12 tables,"
    },
    {
      "id": 79,
      "start": 198.16,
      "end": 200.32,
      "text": "you're trying to join in a single query."
    },
    {
      "id": 80,
      "start": 200.32,
      "end": 202.56,
      "text": "There's a flag you specify what that code off is,"
    },
    {
      "id": 81,
      "start": 202.56,
      "end": 203.76,
      "text": "but by default,"
    },
    {
      "id": 82,
      "start": 203.76,
      "end": 207.12,
      "text": "you don't get this unless it's a 13-way join or higher."
    },
    {
      "id": 83,
      "start": 207.12,
      "end": 208.12,
      "text": "So let's take that,"
    },
    {
      "id": 84,
      "start": 208.12,
      "end": 209.48,
      "text": "say we have some random query,"
    },
    {
      "id": 85,
      "start": 209.48,
      "end": 212.12,
      "text": "we have a bunch of random combinations of join orders"
    },
    {
      "id": 86,
      "start": 212.12,
      "end": 214.6,
      "text": "and join algorithms,"
    },
    {
      "id": 87,
      "start": 214.6,
      "end": 217.4,
      "text": "you pick first you cost all of them,"
    },
    {
      "id": 88,
      "start": 217.4,
      "end": 219.0,
      "text": "keep track of the one with the lowest cost,"
    },
    {
      "id": 89,
      "start": 219.0,
      "end": 220.0,
      "text": "up in the corner,"
    },
    {
      "id": 90,
      "start": 220.0,
      "end": 221.48,
      "text": "which is keep track of the best one I've ever seen,"
    },
    {
      "id": 91,
      "start": 221.48,
      "end": 224.92,
      "text": "throw away the one that has the worst cost,"
    },
    {
      "id": 92,
      "start": 226.0,
      "end": 229.96,
      "text": "and then permute some portion of the query plans"
    },
    {
      "id": 93,
      "start": 229.96,
      "end": 231.24,
      "text": "of the ones you keep around,"
    },
    {
      "id": 94,
      "start": 231.24,
      "end": 234.44,
      "text": "and then the next generation you populate those."
    },
    {
      "id": 95,
      "start": 234.44,
      "end": 235.32,
      "text": "Do the same thing,"
    },
    {
      "id": 96,
      "start": 235.32,
      "end": 236.88,
      "text": "check which one has the lowest cost,"
    },
    {
      "id": 97,
      "start": 236.88,
      "end": 237.72,
      "text": "this one does,"
    },
    {
      "id": 98,
      "start": 237.72,
      "end": 239.2,
      "text": "so that's not near our best cost,"
    },
    {
      "id": 99,
      "start": 239.2,
      "end": 242.12,
      "text": "throw away the weakest one,"
    },
    {
      "id": 100,
      "start": 242.12,
      "end": 243.52,
      "text": "the weakest of this generation,"
    },
    {
      "id": 101,
      "start": 243.52,
      "end": 244.56,
      "text": "permute them,"
    },
    {
      "id": 102,
      "start": 244.56,
      "end": 246.28,
      "text": "and then so forth, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 103,
      "start": 246.28,
      "end": 247.12,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 104,
      "start": 247.12,
      "end": 248.6,
      "text": "These are the last costs that are estimated costs."
    },
    {
      "id": 105,
      "start": 248.6,
      "end": 249.44,
      "text": "These are estimated costs,"
    },
    {
      "id": 106,
      "start": 249.44,
      "end": 250.72,
      "text": "why would you be realized?"
    },
    {
      "id": 107,
      "start": 250.72,
      "end": 251.96,
      "text": "I don't think they're like,"
    },
    {
      "id": 108,
      "start": 251.96,
      "end": 254.2,
      "text": "take these random queries and then plug each random one"
    },
    {
      "id": 109,
      "start": 254.2,
      "end": 255.2,
      "text": "and then pick the best one."
    },
    {
      "id": 110,
      "start": 255.2,
      "end": 256.04,
      "text": "Yeah, this is like,"
    },
    {
      "id": 111,
      "start": 256.04,
      "end": 257.92,
      "text": "this is all within the query optimizer,"
    },
    {
      "id": 112,
      "start": 257.92,
      "end": 259.8,
      "text": "only Mongo does that,"
    },
    {
      "id": 113,
      "start": 259.8,
      "end": 261.0,
      "text": "runs everyone."
    },
    {
      "id": 114,
      "start": 261.08,
      "end": 262.56,
      "text": "This is like using the cost one as well,"
    },
    {
      "id": 115,
      "start": 262.56,
      "end": 263.56,
      "text": "so it's all right next week."
    },
    {
      "id": 116,
      "start": 263.56,
      "end": 264.4,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 117,
      "start": 264.4,
      "end": 266.88,
      "text": "So in this case,"
    },
    {
      "id": 118,
      "start": 266.88,
      "end": 269.16,
      "text": "how does it come to the first generation?"
    },
    {
      "id": 119,
      "start": 269.16,
      "end": 270.6,
      "text": "So how do you come up with the first generation?"
    },
    {
      "id": 120,
      "start": 270.6,
      "end": 271.88,
      "text": "It's random."
    },
    {
      "id": 121,
      "start": 271.88,
      "end": 272.88,
      "text": "Even the first generation,"
    },
    {
      "id": 122,
      "start": 272.88,
      "end": 274.48,
      "text": "I think the first generation random,"
    },
    {
      "id": 123,
      "start": 274.48,
      "end": 275.32,
      "text": "and after that,"
    },
    {
      "id": 124,
      "start": 275.32,
      "end": 277.68,
      "text": "it's specifically picking things I could."
    },
    {
      "id": 125,
      "start": 277.68,
      "end": 279.0,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 126,
      "start": 279.0,
      "end": 282.36,
      "text": "Right, so I know I have to join RS and T,"
    },
    {
      "id": 127,
      "start": 282.36,
      "end": 284.56,
      "text": "so let me give different join owners,"
    },
    {
      "id": 128,
      "start": 284.56,
      "end": 286.4,
      "text": "different physical operators,"
    },
    {
      "id": 129,
      "start": 286.4,
      "end": 288.48,
      "text": "and then just try it out."
    },
    {
      "id": 130,
      "start": 291.96,
      "end": 293.64,
      "text": "So I know in the case of Postgres,"
    },
    {
      "id": 131,
      "start": 293.64,
      "end": 296.32,
      "text": "like they make sure that the random permutations"
    },
    {
      "id": 132,
      "start": 296.32,
      "end": 297.24,
      "text": "is deterministic,"
    },
    {
      "id": 133,
      "start": 297.24,
      "end": 298.72,
      "text": "because you don't want to be,"
    },
    {
      "id": 134,
      "start": 298.72,
      "end": 300.84,
      "text": "if you throw the same query at it again,"
    },
    {
      "id": 135,
      "start": 300.84,
      "end": 301.56,
      "text": "you want to end up,"
    },
    {
      "id": 136,
      "start": 301.56,
      "end": 302.32,
      "text": "and you're using it running this,"
    },
    {
      "id": 137,
      "start": 302.32,
      "end": 304.88,
      "text": "and you want to end up with the same permutation, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 138,
      "start": 304.88,
      "end": 306.48,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 139,
      "start": 306.48,
      "end": 308.24,
      "text": "It seems like a good idea."
    },
    {
      "id": 140,
      "start": 308.24,
      "end": 310.04,
      "text": "Seems like a good idea."
    },
    {
      "id": 141,
      "start": 310.04,
      "end": 310.88,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "id": 142,
      "start": 310.88,
      "end": 315.16,
      "text": "It's a good idea because if you have 13 joins,"
    },
    {
      "id": 143,
      "start": 315.16,
      "end": 317.4,
      "text": "like that's a lot of them."
    },
    {
      "id": 144,
      "start": 317.4,
      "end": 320.08,
      "text": "So going from a random algorithm,"
    },
    {
      "id": 145,
      "start": 320.44,
      "end": 322.44,
      "text": "approaching it from a,"
    },
    {
      "id": 146,
      "start": 322.44,
      "end": 325.04,
      "text": "it almost exhausts it from the tree,"
    },
    {
      "id": 147,
      "start": 325.04,
      "end": 327.12,
      "text": "top down the water bottom of one,"
    },
    {
      "id": 148,
      "start": 327.12,
      "end": 328.72,
      "text": "is just too slow,"
    },
    {
      "id": 149,
      "start": 328.72,
      "end": 331.48,
      "text": "and you're unlikely to get the right join for everything,"
    },
    {
      "id": 150,
      "start": 331.48,
      "end": 333.92,
      "text": "one of them, and you're on it."
    },
    {
      "id": 151,
      "start": 333.92,
      "end": 335.44,
      "text": "So if you go from a random algorithm,"
    },
    {
      "id": 152,
      "start": 335.44,
      "end": 336.52,
      "text": "and you're on a higher,"
    },
    {
      "id": 153,
      "start": 336.52,
      "end": 337.36,
      "text": "is that not too long?"
    },
    {
      "id": 154,
      "start": 337.36,
      "end": 338.2,
      "text": "I just put one thing in,"
    },
    {
      "id": 155,
      "start": 338.2,
      "end": 339.04,
      "text": "I don't even think."
    },
    {
      "id": 156,
      "start": 340.96,
      "end": 341.96,
      "text": "From the first situation,"
    },
    {
      "id": 157,
      "start": 341.96,
      "end": 344.8,
      "text": "it seems like this should work, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 158,
      "start": 344.8,
      "end": 346.24,
      "text": "There's an engineering cost to making sure"
    },
    {
      "id": 159,
      "start": 346.24,
